abstract: Ms. Kauders, who started auditioning at about 60, appeared in “Witness,” “American Splendor,” “The Sopranos” and more in “old lady” roles.
snippet: Ms. Kauders, who started auditioning at about 60, appeared in “Witness,” “American Splendor,” “The Sopranos” and more in “old lady” roles.
lead_paragraph: Many of her bit parts in movies and television series described her only as “old Jewish lady” — the kind of role casting directors were apt to give such a late-blooming professional actress as Sylvia Kauders.

abstract: “Catastrophe” starts Season 2 by finding Sharon and Rob coping with a second child. And Meryl Streep rocks out in “Ricki and the Flash.”
snippet: “Catastrophe” starts Season 2 by finding Sharon and Rob coping with a second child. And Meryl Streep rocks out in “Ricki and the Flash.”
lead_paragraph: “Catastrophe” zooms ahead in Season 2 to find Sharon and Rob, those accidental parents, steering into the skid of life. Meryl Streep rocks out in a Bo Derek hairstyle in “Ricki and the Flash.” And Al Jazeera America presents its last documentary before going off the air on Tuesday.

abstract: It’s great to see an experimental approach to these galleries, but putting everything in a blender also has a homogenizing effect.
snippet: It’s great to see an experimental approach to these galleries, but putting everything in a blender also has a homogenizing effect.
lead_paragraph: Since reopening in its expanded building in 2004, the Museum of Modern Art has shaken itself up in numerous ways, some for better, others for worse. Worse includes a penchant for atrium-oriented spectacle, like Tilda Swinton sleeping in a vitrine; earsplitting music at seemingly every opening; and the debacle that was its halfhearted Björk retrospective.

abstract: Defense lawyers and jurors have vigorously questioned a strategy by the New York Police Department that prizes the pursuit of the addicts who use drugs over the people who supply them.
snippet: Defense lawyers and jurors have vigorously questioned a strategy by the New York Police Department that prizes the pursuit of the addicts who use drugs over the people who supply them.
lead_paragraph: The 55-year-old crack addict counted his change outside a Harlem liquor store. He had just over a dollar, leaving him 35 cents short of the cheapest mini-bottle.
